data.name: label_NotReadyToUpdate.Text
data.value:
To update navX-Model Firmware, the device must be in Firmware Update Mode.
1. Disconnect the navX-Model device from the PC USB port. 2. Ensure the device has completely powered down (the RED "3.3V LED must be off). 3. While holding down the 'CAL' button, re-connect the board to the PC USB port. 4. After the board has powered up, release the 'CAL' button.
When in Firmware Update Mode, only the RED '3.3V" LED will be on.

data.name: label_ReadyToUpdate.Text
data.value:
navX-Model device is currently in Firmware Update Mode.
Press the 'Update navX-Model Firmware' button to begin.
Do not disconnect the navX-Model device from the PC USB port until the firmware update is complete.
Once completed, the navX-Model device will automatically restart and enter Operational Mode. At that time, you can verify the Currently-loaded navX-Model Firmware Version.
